## Discarding the duplicates

If you simply want to discard the duplicates, use a [`Set&lt;T&gt;`][2] instead of a [`List&lt;T&gt;`][3]. From the [`Set&lt;T&gt;`][2] documentation:

&gt; A collection that contains no duplicate elements.

To discard the duplicates, you can use:

```java
List&lt;Integer&gt; numbers = Arrays.asList(1, 2, 3, 3, 4, 4);
Set&lt;Integer&gt; unique = new HashSet&lt;&gt;(numbers);
```

You also could use:

```java
List&lt;Integer&gt; numbers = Arrays.asList(1, 2, 3, 3, 4, 4);
List&lt;Integer&gt; unique = numbers.stream()
        .distinct()
        .collect(Collectors.toList());
```

## Finding the duplicates

If you have a list and want to extract the duplicates, you can use the following:

```java
List&lt;Integer&gt; numbers = Arrays.asList(1, 2, 3, 3, 4, 4);
List&lt;Integer&gt; duplicates = numbers.stream()
        .filter(n -&gt; Collections.frequency(numbers, n) &gt; 1)
        .distinct()
        .collect(Collectors.toList());
```

## Using Hibernate Validator

If you are using [Hibernate Validator][7], a Bean Validation implementation, you could use [`@UniqueElements`][1] to validate that every element in the collection is unique.

To use it, ensure your list is annotated with [`@UniqueElements`][1]:

```java
@Data
public class LotteryBet {

    @UniqueElements
    private List&lt;Integer&gt; numbers;
}
```

Then ensure your controller is annotated with [`@Validated`][4] and the `lotteryBet` parameter is annotated with both [`@RequestBody`][5] and [`@Valid`][6]:

```java
@Validated
@RestController
@RequestMapping(&quot;/lottery&quot;)
public class LotteryController {

    @PostMapping(path = &quot;/bets&quot;, consumes = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)
    public ResponseEntity&lt;Void&gt; bet(@RequestBody @Valid LotteryBet lotteryBet) {
        ...
    }
}
```

A request such as the one shown below will return `400` along with some details about the error:

```http
POST /lottery/bets HTTP/1.1
Host: example.org
Content-Type: application/json

{
  &quot;numbers&quot;: [1, 2, 3, 3, 4, 4]
}
```


  [1]: https://docs.jboss.org/hibernate/stable/validator/api/org/hibernate/validator/constraints/UniqueElements.html
  [2]: https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/12/docs/api/java.base/java/util/Set.html
  [3]: https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/12/docs/api/java.base/java/util/List.html
  [4]: https://docs.spring.io/spring/docs/current/javadoc-api/org/springframework/validation/annotation/Validated.html
